            <title>How Alloy Wheels are Manufactured</title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;
	Aluminum alloy wheels not only are more attractive than standard steel wheels, but they also are a fraction of the weight and therefore require less energy to rotate. This contributes to greater fuel efficiency as well as better handling, acceleration and braking. This 5-minute video shows the manufacturing process for aluminum alloy wheels, from casting and molding to heat treating, machining and painting.&lt;/p&gt;
