            <title>Caterpillar, Modustri Form Alliance</title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;
	Caterpillar Inc. recently entered into a strategic alliance with Modustri to help customers optimize parts performance and further understand the health of their equipment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Caterpillar and Modustri will work together to develop innovations that enhance customers&amp;#39; abilities to measure wear on parts, which in turn will help them optimize their fleets more effectively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;quot;We are at the forefront of a revolution in the heavy equipment industry,&amp;quot; said Greg Folley, vice president of the newly formed analytics and innovation division at Caterpillar. &amp;quot;Emerging technologies are changing the way we can help customers maintain a competitive advantage and achieve new levels of equipment productivity and profitability. Our alliance with Modustri will be key in making this happen.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	By utilizing Web-based and mobile platforms, the companies will deliver simplified processes that provide customers accurate and immediate access to useful, real-time data while still in the field.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;quot;We&amp;#39;ve seen how mobile technology can change the behaviors of customers,&amp;quot; said Brian Steketee, founder and CEO of Modustri. &amp;quot;Now we can see groundbreaking hardware and software that can help dealers interact with customers, build trust and plan ahead for maintenance and parts replacements.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	In the coming months, Caterpillar will collaborate with Modustri and the Cat dealer network to create equipment wear management technologies through Web-based and mobile platforms, which will then be available for customer use.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	For more information, visit &lt;a href="http://www.caterpillar.com"&gt;www.caterpillar.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/manufacturing/~4/bNT2NMbO8EY" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
