            <title>Wood-Mizer Announces New Indiana Manufacturing Plant</title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;
	Sawmill manufacturer Wood-Mizer recently announced plans to build a new 85,000-square-foot production facility in Batesville, Indiana. Scheduled for completion in December 2015, the plant will produce Wood-Mizer&amp;#39;s portable sawmills, industrial sawmills and blade maintenance equipment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The new facility, which will replace the company&amp;#39;s current sawmill manufacturing plant in New Point, Indiana, will bring 120 jobs to the area while creating 15 additional job opportunities for the community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;quot;The new Wood-Mizer manufacturing facility is an important investment that will bring jobs and opportunity for future economic growth to our community,&amp;quot; said Batesville mayor Rick Fledderman. &amp;quot;We are very eager to work with Wood-Mizer and look forward to our continued partnership in the future.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The city of Batesville encouraged Wood-Mizer to build the production plant in Batesville by offering an incentive package that included benefits such as project financing. Wood-Mizer has announced an $8.4-million investment in the land, building, equipment and improvements for the new manufacturing facility.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;quot;Being involved with the Southeast Indiana community for more than 30 years, we wanted to establish an opportunity for expansion for both Wood-Mizer and the local economy,&amp;quot; said Wood-Mizer&amp;#39;s Darryl Floyd. &amp;quot;While becoming one of the largest companies in Batesville, Wood-Mizer is excited to continue manufacturing sawmills in a more efficient and larger capacity at this location, and we&amp;#39;d like to thank the city of Batesville for their assistance in making this opportunity possible.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	For more information, visit &lt;a href="http://www.woodmizer.com"&gt;www.woodmizer.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/manufacturing/~4/MuAThE0qSOs" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
