            <title>Ilapak to Build U.S. Manufacturing Plant</title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;
	Packaging equipment manufacturer Ilapak recently announced that it is expanding its U.S. manufacturing with the development of a new state-of-the-art production facility in northwest Arkansas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The new facility will help Ilapak meet growing U.S. demand and allow the company to extend the range of solutions it manufactures in the United States.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;quot;We&amp;#39;ve always tailored our solutions to reflect our customers&amp;#39; specific needs in different parts of the world,&amp;quot; says Ilapak&amp;#39;s Guy Levy. &amp;quot;We are now taking this approach to the next level with a wider range of U.S.-made Ilapak solutions manufactured in a brand new world-class facility.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The 80,000-square-foot facility will be centrally located in Lowell, Arkansas, in close proximity to the local airport and major transportation corridor. The new temperature-controlled manufacturing area will enable Ilapak to test conditions closer to a customer&amp;#39;s own factory conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The facility will also house a research and development team focused on engineering solutions for the North American market, as well as a quick-response service center and a customer innovation and demonstration area. An additional 20,000 square feet of manufacturing capacity is also planned to allow for expansion in line with the company&amp;#39;s growth strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Headquartered in Switzerland, Ilapak also operates three manufacturing plants in Italy, Switzerland and China.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	For more information, visit &lt;a href="http://www.ilapak.com"&gt;www.ilapak.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/manufacturing/~4/bZNoXL7ZM7U" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
