            <title>Giti Tire to Build New Manufacturing Plant in South Carolina</title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;
	Giti Tire recently announced plans to build a new manufacturing plant in Chester, S.C., to meet growing demand in North America. The $560-million facility is expected to generate 1,700 new jobs over the next 10 years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;quot;The new facility will combine a manufacturing plant and distribution center with total building area estimated to be 1.8 million square feet,&amp;quot; said Tom McNamara, executive vice president of sales and marketing for Giti Tire (USA) Ltd. &amp;quot;The first phase of production capacity is expected to be 5 million tires annually. Giti Tire plans to further increase production capacity in response to future market demand and conditions.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The plant, which will produce passenger and light truck tires for the replacement and original equipment markets, will be built with a focus on maintaining a healthy balance with the environment and following Giti Tire&amp;#39;s green initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;quot;Chester County is an excellent location for Giti Tire, offering an extensive and efficient infrastructure network including interstate highways, rail, close proximity to airports and a major metropolitan area to support the company&amp;#39;s needs and growth for many years to come,&amp;quot; said Lei Huai Chin, managing director of Giti Tire Group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Giti Tire currently operates eight manufacturing plants while producing a broad range of tire products for customers in more than 100 countries worldwide.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	For more information, visit &lt;a href="http://www.gtradial.com"&gt;www.gtradial.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/manufacturing/~4/jsESpDqTTT4" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
